# Splitwallet frontend — environment configuration
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy this file to one of:
#   .env.development.local   ← dev-only overrides, gitignored (recommended)
#   .env.development         ← committed dev defaults (currently points at localhost)
#   .env.production.local    ← prod build overrides
# Vite loads them automatically based on `npm run dev` vs `npm run build`.


# ── DEV: proxy target ────────────────────────────
# `npm run dev` boots a Vite proxy at http://localhost:5173 that forwards
#   /authentication/*, /account/*, /transaction/*, /ingestion/*
# to whatever VITE_GATEWAY_URL points at. This avoids CORS during dev and means
# the SPA itself can keep using same-origin paths.
#
# Examples:
#   VITE_GATEWAY_URL=http://localhost:8080            # local gateway
#   VITE_GATEWAY_URL=https://api.staging.example.com  # remote gateway
VITE_GATEWAY_URL=http://localhost:8080


# ── PROD: direct backend URL (optional) ──────────
# When set, axios prepends this to every API call instead of going same-origin.
# Use it in production builds where there's no Vite proxy in front of the SPA.
# Leave it unset in dev (the proxy handles routing).
# CORS must be configured on the gateway/server for the SPA's origin.
#
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.example.com


# ── Firebase (REQUIRED for sign-in) ──────────────
# The app authenticates via Google / Apple OAuth using the Firebase Web SDK
# (src/lib/firebase.ts), and the same values power the 401 → silent-refresh
# interceptor in src/api/refresh.ts. Copy these from the Firebase console:
#   Project settings → General → Your apps → SDK setup and configuration.
# Use the SAME Firebase project the backend's Admin SDK is configured against.
#
# Enable the Google provider under Authentication → Sign-in method, and add
# your origin (e.g. localhost) under Authentication → Settings → Authorized
# domains. (Apple sign-in is not wired up in the UI yet — it additionally needs
# an Apple Developer Services ID configured in Firebase.)
#
# VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=AIza...
# VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=your-project.firebaseapp.com
# VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project
